Need for Speed: The Run is competing all over America.
Reviews
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of inappropriate neglects for a routine trip during tomorrow’s shift.
To some extent, expectations have been met, but this is of no use, if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new release, to which the title is added The Run, aroused great expectations already before its premiere.
It promised it would give new airs to the old racing saga Need for Speed and, as a result of what was shown, it appears as a game that shouldn’t end up being an action genre again.
We are also curious about how the scenes would look, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As often happens in the NFS series, the results do not vary much over what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in total computing points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already been appearing in the series for years.
In fact, errors can not be called errors, but rather the incomprehensible mistake of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
He introduces you to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get the first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
From this it follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasant to see, although the technical level of the chart is equivalent to that of previous series deliveries.
Therefore, it is nothing from the other world.
But the desert ride, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, you must be careful not to be buried by an avalanche in the mountains.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (classic timed duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this sometimes appears the police, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are a lot less landscapes in the game than you might expect (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the above-mentioned context, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the footprints of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer much, but it cannot be claimed to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can now search elsewhere.
But a race conceived with a lot of action suits this driving style quite well, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
Until here, everything in order.
But the problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the right of driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
From games of this kind you cannot expect to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that when making a very tight overtaking or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouets.
Or even it is completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can get you in a bad mood.
Resets are scheduled in such a way that when you suffer an accident or get out of the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
In each race, however, only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is nothing more than a help in case something doesn’t go well, but it’s not very trustworthy.
Sometimes, not even resetting helps, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A major disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you find somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrived five minutes before or after.
This makes it rage especially in situations, when you see two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances smoothly, but when you arrive, you must either turn or brake.
It’s the same when you arrive, because it’s programmed because the “surprise” will always happen in front of your noses.
Adversaries also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always ahead of you in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars that come in front, so at first you can brush the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you immediately.
And it’s a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so that it doesn’t catch the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during racing.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline suppliers next to the road, because precisely there you have to change your car, although in the vast majority of cases what you have will suffice.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition to the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know through the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
On reaching the upper level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and makes available other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is done.
With the car you reach the tunnel of the metro (pass), where you get to run in the dark through the lanes (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, from behind you comes the metro convoy and is taken ahead without more.
In the editorial we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, whether during the game programming none even thought a little or whether the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even proud.
It is a shame that, in the most tense moments, the quality of the image is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This affects mostly accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of tastes.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game for his music alone.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely foolish errors, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but be prepared because errors will hit you in the eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
Carolina University choirs will participate in the concert "Students of Velvet".
The joint celebration of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival Festa Academica.
During the same time, twenty corals from high schools and universities will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"Carolina University has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the committee of the festival is the rector Václav Hampl,” said Jakub Čaloun, head of the organization.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the high school choir concert, which will be held on March 17 at 2 p.m. in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The show is attended by Czech jazzist Karel Růžička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady will be held the concert "Students of Velvet", in which will participate university choirs, including the choir of Carolina Uninversity.
The academic festival aims not only to dignifiedly celebrate the International Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choir music to the public at the highest level and to encourage collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the events were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the Carolina University, Václav Hampl.
The festival will run between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised student shows and morning concerts.
Interested parties can find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
