We all love and love to create music.
We are lucky to go to places in the world where we always wanted to go.
Things couldn't be better for us.
What did it mean for you to have been a fundamental part of the rise of grunge?
It has always been an honor to be part of that big band.
We are very friends with the people of Soundgarden, Mudhoney and Alice in Chains.
It’s surprising when a movement arises from a group of friends and it’s rare.
From time to time, a band of a city emerges, but it is much stranger when five or ten bands leave the same city at the same time.
We are proud and honored to be part of the Seattle group.
We still play with some of them from time to time.
