An official comitiva, headed by Uruguayan President José Mujica, and composed of several ministers and businessmen, will begin a visit to Mexico on Tuesday in order to expand trade between the two nations and address political issues in the region.
Mujica will meet next Wednesday with his Mexican peer, Felipe Calderón, highlight of an extensive agenda of meetings with political, commercial authorities and a meeting with the collectivity of Uruguayan residents in Mexico, according to the agenda disseminated by the Uruguayan Presidency.
