Location of impact.
The impact coordinates and the latest radar aircraft record coincide, probably before the impact there was no loss of control or alteration in the flight path.
Dispersion of aircraft debris in a reduced area:
The information available so far suggests that the impact occurred on a straight and side trajectory.
The scattering pattern of the aircraft’s debris allows to assume that the helicopter was impacted on the ground under conditions of structural integrity.
No evidence of fire or explosion has been detected:
At the site of the disaster there is still no evidence revealed on the remains of the ship of some kind of explosion or fire.
